headline: Assessing Intuitive Surgical (ISRG) Valuation After Recent Share Price Weakness
summary: Why Intuitive Surgical stock is on investors’ radar today Intuitive Surgical (ISRG) is drawing attention after a period of weaker recent share returns, with the stock down around 8% over the past week and 19% over the past year. See our latest analysis for Intuitive Surgical. The recent 1-month share price return of a 15.52% decline and 1-year total shareholder return of a 19.02% decline point to fading momentum. headline: Can Intuitive Surgical Sustain Robust Top-line Growth in 2026?
summary: ISRG posts 20.5% revenue growth in 2025, driven by higher procedure volumes and da Vinci 5 adoption, and guides for 13-15% procedure growth in 2026.
